Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery vessel, probably a dinos; dull light grey fabric with mica inclusions; worn dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Fabris, varying thickness and letter forms suggest this is from the same piece as 1888,0601.429.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.154)
